Run some stats and make a table here

Arm x fu_stat chi square table (1 = lived, 2 = died)

mockdata %>% 
  tabyl(arm, fu_stat) %>% 
  adorn_totals("row") %>% # can also do "col", or c("row", "col")
  adorn_percentages("row") %>% 
  adorn_pct_formatting() %>% 
  adorn_ns() %>% 
  knitr::kable()
arm 1 2
A: IFL 4.2% (18) 95.8% (410)
F: FOLFOX 14.3% (99) 85.7% (592)
G: IROX 6.8% (26) 93.2% (354)
Total 9.5% (143) 90.5% (1356) 
mockdata %>% 
  mutate(fu_stat = as.factor(fu_stat)) %>% 
  specify(fu_stat ~ arm) %>% # alt: response = fu_stat, explanatory = arm
  calculate(stat = "Chisq")
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##    stat
##   <dbl>
## 1  35.7
mockdata %>% 
  specify(formula = fu_stat ~ arm, success = "1") %>% 
  hypothesize(null = "independence") %>% 
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "permute") %>% 
  calculate(stat = "diff in props", order = c("0", "1"))

make bar/lollipop chart of proportions here (% survived)

Start with a barplot for percent survival tag it as panel A for a multipanel plot

prop_surv <- mockdata %>% 
  count(arm, fu_stat, name = "by_surv") %>% 
  add_count(arm, wt = by_surv, name = "arm_total") %>% 
  mutate(prop = by_surv/arm_total) %>% 
  filter(fu_stat == 1)
ggplot(prop_surv, aes(x = arm, y = prop, fill = arm)) +
  geom_col(colour = "gray") +
  labs(y= "Percent Survived", x= "Study Arm", tag ="A") +
  scale_fill_scico_d(palette = 'lapaz') +
  scale_y_continuous(labels=scales::percent)

Then distribution plot of survival time (in days censored)

ggplot(mockdata) +
  aes(x=arm, y = fu_time, fill=arm) +
  geom_jitter(width =0.25, alpha=0.5) +
  geom_violin(alpha =0.7) +
  labs(y= "Survival Time in \nDays (Censored)", x= "Study Arm", tag = "B") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_fill_scico_d(palette = 'lapaz') ->
